<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.5555in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Acid Spray</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:9.3125in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step Number: R=
ank +
DEX</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Mundane<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Water—Acid.<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Just below the
creature’s mouth is an organ that can fire a spray of concentrated irrita=
nt.
This substance is not corrosive, but causes extremely painful rashes and
swelling if it hits exposed flesh. The creature makes an Acid Spray Test
against the target’s Physical Defense. The power’s range is the creatur=
e’s Rank
× 6 yards (Rank × 3 hexes). If the test succeeds, the target is hit with =
acidic
spray. Any character hit by the irritant must make a Willpower Test against=
 the
Acid Spray Test result. If this test fails, the target falls to the ground,
writhing in agony for a number of rounds equal to the Acid Spray Rank. The
target may make a Willpower Test against the Acid Spray Test result each ro=
und
to recover. The acid’s potency decreases over time; subtract –1 from the
Difficulty Number of the Willpower Test each round after the first.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.9784in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Aid Summoner</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.4506in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041=
in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Strength
Rating</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Aid Summon=
er
power allows a spirit to enhance its summoner’s magical abilities. To act=
ivate
this power, the spirit’s summoner takes Strain equal to the spirit’s St=
rength
Rating. For the duration of the power, the summoner may add a bonus equal to
the spirit’s Strength Rating to any of his magical ability steps when mak=
ing
tests. This includes talents such as Spellcasting, Thread Weaving and
Willforce. This bonus may be applied to different abilities, as chosen by t=
he
summoner, but only one ability each round. For example, during one round the
summoner may boost his Spellcasting talent, while in the next round he may
boost his Willforce talent. Each time the summoner uses the bonus on an Act=
ion
Test he takes 2 Strain. Each use of the Aid Summoner power lasts for a numb=
er
of minutes equal to the spirit’s Strength Rating.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.9187in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Animate Dead</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + W=
IL</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Animate De=
ad
power allows a Horror to place an undead spirit into a corpse or cadaver,
resulting in the creation of a cadaver man (p. 278). The Horror touches a
portion of the deceased body and makes an Animate Dead Test against the
deceased target’s Spell Defense. If the test succeeds, the dead man is ra=
ised
to unlife for a number of days equal to the Horror’s Animate Dead Step, t=
urning
him into a cadaver man under the Horror’s control. The Horror can directly
control the cadaver man at a distance equal to its Animate Dead Step × 20 =
yards
(10 hexes). Though the Horror must concentrate to control the dead, it need=
 not
make any tests to give the cadaver man orders. Because cadaver men created =
with
this power are telepathically linked to the Horror, its commands to them do=
 not
depend on speech or line of sight. The Horror may use blood magic to extend=
 the
power’s duration. For 1 Blood Magic Damage, the Horror can keep the cadav=
er man
animated for a year and a day. At the end of this time, the cadaver man
collapses into dust unless the Horror continues to extend the blood magic. =
This
damage can be healed once the cadaver man is destroyed or the power ends,
whichever occurs first.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:2.0472in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Armored Scales=
</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.4506in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041=
in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + T=
OU
(see text)</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: NA</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>A dragon’s a=
rmored
hide provides great physical and magical protection against attack. Use the
Armored Scales Step Number as the dragon’s Physical Armor Rating. Add the
dragon’s Armored Scales Rank to its Mystic Armor Rating. Only attacks that
score an Extraordinary result against the dragon’s Physical Defense achie=
ve an
Armor-Defeating Hit. Mystic Armor protects against magical attacks in the s=
ame
way; any attacks made against the dragon’s Spell Defense must achieve an
Extraordinary result to bypass the dragon’s Mystic Armor.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:2.3076in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Astral Camoufl=
age</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + W=
IL</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Some Horrors h=
ave
the ability to hide their presence in astral space, and can use this power =
to
camouflage their astral imprint. The Horror makes an Astral Camouflage Test,
the result of which becomes the Detection Difficulty for Perception and any
Astral Sensing Tests. If the Horror engages in combat or moves faster than =
half
its normal Movement Rate, the camouflage is disrupted. Though its features
appear blurry and indistinct, it can be seen normally, and will remain visi=
ble
until the end of the round in which it slows down. Each use of the Astral
Camouflage power lasts for a number of hours equal to the Horror’s rank in
Astral Camouflage.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.7388in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Astral Portal<=
/p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.4506in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041=
in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Strength
Rating</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Ally spirits o=
nly.
This power enables a spirit to create a portal through which Namegivers can
enter astral space. The portal remains open for a number of minutes equal to
the spirit’s Strength Rating × 10. Note that the portal is two-way, allo=
wing
entry into and exit from astral space.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.6402in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Astral Sight</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + P=
ER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Like dragons, =
almost
all Horrors possess astral sight. To use this ability, the Horror makes an
Astral Sight Test. The gamemaster then compares the result against the Spell
Defense of each object or being within Astral Sight Rank × 10 yards (5 hex=
es)
of the Horror and in its line of sight. If the test succeeds, the Horror can
see the target’s astral image.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.7347in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Aura of Awe</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + C=
HA</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Aura of Awe
power allows a Horror to alter the attitudes of other characters toward it.=
 To
use this power, the Horror makes an Aura of Awe Test against the target’s
Social Defense. The range of this power is the Horror’s line of sight. The
result level achieved determines the Attitude of the target. On a Poor resu=
lt,
the target adopts a Neutral attitude toward the Horror. On an Average resul=
t,
the target adopts a Friendly attitude. On a Good result, the target becomes
Loyal. An Excellent or better result means the target is Awestruck. The eff=
ect
lasts until the target has been out of the Horror’s presence for a year a=
nd a
day, or until the Horror directly or otherwise obviously injures the target.
When a player character is affected by the Aura of Awe, the gamemaster may
secretly instruct the player to run the character appropriately or may
temporarily take over decisions for the player until the power ends or is
dispelled.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.5375in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.8958in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Blinding Glare=
</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.5375in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step Number: R=
ank +
PER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Magical<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This magical
eyelight creates a cone of steady light that extends to a distance listed w=
ith
the creature’s description, widening to a 45-degree arc at the far end (t=
hus
creating a cone). The creature’s Blinding Glare Test result is compared a=
gainst
the Spell Defense of each target within the cone of effect. If successful, =
the
target is Dazzled (Player’s Guide p. 226) for a number of rounds equal to=
 the
creature’s Blinding Glare Rank. The result level determines the degree of
blindness—Partial for an Average result; Full for a Good result; Complete=
 for
an Excellent or Extraordinary result.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.5513in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.6833in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Blood Veins</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.5513in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step Number: R=
ank +
STR</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Mundane<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Blood Veins
power allows the creature to push small veins into victims it is touching,
drawing away and deriving its sustenance from the victim’s blood and flui=
ds.
Each minute it is attached to the victim, the creature makes a Blood Veins =
Test
to determine how much damage it inflicts. No armor protects against this
damage.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.859in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Bone Shaping</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step Number: R=
ank +
WIL</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Simple=
</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Magical<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Bone Shapi=
ng
power is especially dangerous, as it derives from Horror magic. To use this
power, the creature makes a Spellcasting Test against the target’s Spell
Defense. If using its bone shaping ability on a Horror-marked target, the
creature adds a +2 bonus to its Spellcasting Test, courtesy of its affinity
with and its understanding of the intricacies of Horror magic. The power’s
range is the creature’s Rank × 2 yards (Rank × 1 hexes). If the test su=
cceeds,
the creature begins reshaping the victim’s bones at will. The creature ma=
kes a
Bone Shaping Test to determine how much damage it inflicts. Mystic Armor
protects against this damage. The victim incurs a penalty to his Action Tes=
ts
equal to the creature’s Bone Shaping Rank. The effects can be undone, but=
 only
by being subjected to further use of the Bone Shaping power.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:2.0631in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Breath Weapon<=
/p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step Number: R=
ank +
WIL</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Simple=
</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Magical<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Element as per
creature description, if any.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This power all=
ows a
creature to breathe a damaging substance at its victims, possibly even a
burning one. The exact substance and range is listed with each creature. To
attack with its breath weapon, the creature makes a Spellcasting Test again=
st
the target’s Spell Defense. If the test succeeds, the creature makes a Br=
eath
Weapon Test to determine how much damage is inflicted. Mystic Armor provides
protect ion against this damage. If the substance is burning or acidic in
nature, it continues to bum the character for the next 3 rounds, doing an
additional Step 6 damage every round unless the character puts it out by di=
ving
into a pool of water, somehow neutralizing it (if it is an acid), or
suffocating the flames by other means. For burning substances, the heat fro=
m a
fire this size is equal to a small campfire (see p. 109) and can affect nea=
rby
targets, the victim’s possessions, and the surrounding area.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.5256in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.8104in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Burning Aura</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:6.5256in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: NA</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Magical<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Fire.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

