<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.7138in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Dragonsight</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.4506in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041=
in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + P=
ER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Dragons are
naturally attuned to astral space, allowing them to see astral forms at wil=
l.
To use this power, the dragon makes a Dragonsight Test. If the result of the
test exceeds the Spell Defense of any subject within the dragon’s line of
sight, the dragon can see the astral image of the subject. The Dragonsight
power is a heightened version of the Astral Sight talent. Unlike most
Namegivers, dragons do not have to spend Strain to use it. For more informa=
tion
about the use of Astral Sight and other astral sensing abilities, see the
Workings of Magic chapter in the Player’s Guide, p. 104.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Dragonsight Kn=
acks</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Many dragons d=
evelop
power knacks using their Dragonsight. Any of the Astral Sight talent knacks
from the Talent Knacks chapter of the Player’s Companion, may be learned =
by
dragons as Dragonsight power knacks. Dragons also have some unique Dragonsi=
ght
knacks of their own:</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Item History</=
p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This knack fun=
ctions
exactly like the Item History talent except the dragon uses its Dragonsight
Step in place of the Talent Step, and the dragon needs to study the item for
only a day, not a full week. Use the results of the dragon’s Item History=
 Test
normally for determining an item’s Key Knowledges. Some dragons (including
Icewing) have been known to perform Item History on powerful magical items =
with
high Spell Defenses), in exchange for future favors from adventurers.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Matrix Strike<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>With the Matrix
Strike knack, a dragon can attack a magician’s spell matrices in astral s=
pace,
just like the Matrix Strike talent. To use this power, the dragon must have
first detected the astral image of the target with a Dragonsight Test. The
dragon then makes a Spellcasting Test against the target magician’s Spell
Defense. A successful test damages one of the target’s spell matrices. Dr=
agons
can attack matrices only with their claws when using this power. The target=
’s
Mystic Armor protects against this damage.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Spirit Strike<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This knack all=
ows
the dragon to strike at opponents from astral space, just like the Spirit
Strike talent. To use this power, the dragon must have first detected the
astral image of the target with a Dragonsight Test. The dragon then makes a
Spellcasting Test against the target’s Spell Defense. If successful, the =
dragon
causes normal attack damage. Mystic Armor protects against this damage, but
defensive talents such as Avoid Blow cannot be used to avoid a Spirit Strik=
e.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>True Sight</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Dragons are
difficult to fool, and dragons with this knack are even more so. True Sight
allows a dragon to see through illusions, like the talent of the same name.=
 To
use this knack the dragon makes a Dragonsight Test against the Disbelief
Difficulty of each illusion to overcome it.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>See Illusions =
on p.
139 of the Player’s Guide for more information.</p>

</div>

