<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;border-width:100%'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.9277in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Dragonspeech</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.4506in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041=
in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + P=
ER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>All adult drag=
ons
have the Dragonspeech power. It allows the dragon to transmit its thoughts =
as
speech to any being within the dragon’s line of sight, by making a succes=
sful
Dragonspeech Test against the being’s Spell Defense. The dragon can also =
send
simple images as well as speech through its mental link. A target that wish=
es
to hear the dragon’s mental speech can voluntarily lower its Spell Defens=
e, of
course, although considering the further probing Dragonspeech can be used f=
or,
it is not always wise to trust a dragon. Under normal circumstances, the
gamemaster can assume a dragon’s use of Dragonspeech is successful, unles=
s the
subject has a Spell Defense higher than the dragon’s Spellcasting Step.
Dragonspeech is the natural method of communication for dragons, and they u=
se
it most often among themselves. It is also useful because it transcends
language, allowing a dragon to speak to another being whether or not it
understands the subject’s language.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Dragonspeech K=
nacks</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Most dragons h=
ardly
bother with Dragonspeech except among their own kind, but some have develop=
ed a
number of power knacks using Dragonspeech, including the following:</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Animal Talk</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This knack all=
ows
the dragon to communicate with animals using Dragonspeech. This knack is
commonly used by Leviathans to communicate with other underwater creatures =
and
summon them to protect their underwater domain and lairs.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Read Thoughts<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This knack all=
ows
the dragon to not only project its own thoughts, but to read the surface
thoughts of any being it can see, with a successful Dragonspeech Test again=
st
the subject’s Spell Defense. This permits two-way mental communication be=
tween
the dragon and the subject, transcending language barriers. It also allows =
the
dragon to know what the subject is thinking. A successful Willpower or
Willforce Test against the result of the dragon’s Dragonspeech Test is re=
quired
to successfully hide a thought from the dragon, or to tell a lie. Dragons w=
ith
this knack tend to have great insight into other Namegivers.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Learn Language=
</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>By touching th=
e mind
of a subject using Dragonspeech, the dragon can learn any language the subj=
ect
knows. The dragon makes a Dragonspeech Test against the subject’s Spell
Defense. On an Excellent result, the dragon learns one language the subject
knows, speaking and reading it as fluently as the subject can.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Thought Probe<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Thought Probe =
is one
step more advanced than Read Thoughts. It allows the dragon to sift through=
 the
thoughts and memories of a subject like hunting through a pile of coin and
gems. With a successful Dragonspeech Test, the dragon can probe the subject=
’s mind
for a particular memory or piece of information. The result level of the Te=
st
determines what information the dragon can dig up. An Average result allows=
 the
dragon to locate any memory up to a day old; a Good result up to a week old=
; an
Excellent result up to a year old; an Extraordinary result can locate any
memory, even information the subject is not consciously aware of. In additi=
on
to gaining useful information from unwilling subjects, dragons can use this
knack to read the memories of willing subjects (such as drake and Namegiver
servants). This allows a dragon to directly experience what its servant
experienced.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Second Sight</=
p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Using the Seco=
nd
Sight knack, a dragon can use Dragonspeech to perceive through the senses of
another being, with or without that being’s consent. The dragon must first
establish a connection to the subject via thread magic to use this knack. O=
nce
this is accomplished the dragon may, at any time, make a Dragonspeech Test
against the target’s Spell Defense. If the test succeeds, the dragon gains
access to one of the subject’s senses for each result level achieved. An
Extraordinary result allows the dragon to perceive with all of the subject=
s
senses. The dragon does not have any direct power over the subject using th=
is
knack; in fact, the subject is not even aware the dragon is eavesdropping,
unless the dragon achieves a Poor result on its Dragonspeech Test, in which
case the subject feels a brief sensation of being watched.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Suggestion</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Suggestion=
 knack
allows a dragon to mentally plant a suggestion in the target’s mind, simi=
lar to
a powerful post-hypnotic suggestion. The dragon makes a Dragonspeech Test
against the target’s Spell Defense. If the test succeeds, the dragon may =
implant
a single suggestion. This can be something immediate or it can be triggered=
 by
later circumstances. To overcome the suggestion, the victim must make a
Willpower Test against the dragon’s Dragonspeech Step. Otherwise, the vic=
tim
follows the suggestion as if it were his own idea.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Reweave Mind</=
p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>This is the mo=
st
powerful and sophisticated knack of Dragonspeech—the ability to tear the =
fabric
of a living mind and reweave it to the dragon’s will. The great dragon
Mountainshadow is known to have reached this level of ability, but few other
dragons can hope to do so. With Reweave Mind, a dragon can mentally reshape=
 the
fabric of the subject’s mind, altering, removing or restoring memories,
changing personality and so forth. The process is not fast, even for the
powerful mind of a dragon. Any attempt at Reweave Mind takes at least one h=
our,
longer if the changes are more complex. The dragon makes a Dragonspeech Test
against the subject’s Spell Defense. On an Excellent result, this power a=
llows
the dragon to alter the subject’s memories and such at will. An Extraordi=
nary
result is required to make fundamental changes in personality or vital
memories. Any other result has no effect on the subject. This power can also
literally rebuild a mind shattered by illness or madness.</p>

