<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:7.6041in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.6847in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Spellcasting</=
p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.45in;margin-left:0in;width:7.6041in=
'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>SPIRIT SPELLCA=
STING</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: PER + St=
rength
Rating</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Spellcasti=
ng
power enables spirits to cast spells using raw magic. When casting spells in
this manner, spirits are vulnerable to the same Warping and Damage effects =
as
Namegiver magicians, and they run the same risk of becoming Horror-marked. =
For
these reasons, spirits rarely use this power unless a summoner forces to th=
em
do so. Some (but not all) spirits employ the Thread Weaving and Spell Matrix
powers when casting spells (see Talents, below).</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>HORROR SPELLCA=
STING</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + P=
ER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Almost all Hor=
rors
know how to use spell magic. The ability to manipulate the energies of astr=
al
space is inherent. Though Horrors cast all spells as raw magic (Player’s =
Guide,
p. 136), they take no damage and generally ignore raw magic spells cast by =
other
Horrors. Also, Horrors do not use spell matrices, though they must weave sp=
ell
threads where required. Horrors use the Thread Weaving power when casting
spells in this manner (see Player’s Guide, p. 83).</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>DRAGON SPELLCA=
STING</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + P=
ER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>All adult drag=
ons
know how to use spell magic. The ability to manipulate the energies of astr=
al
space is inherent. Dragons can use their Spellcasting power to cast any spe=
ll
as Raw Magic. The dragon doesn’t need to know the spell, it simply shapes=
 the
astral energy to its will and the spell happens. This is a natural ability =
for
dragons. For a long time, dragons performed all of their magic in this way,
grabbing magical energy and shaping it to their wills. Dragons use the Thre=
ad
Weaving power when casting spells in this manner (Player’s Guide, p. 83).
Hatchlings using this ability must weave all the threads necessary for the
spell they wish to cast. Adult dragons need weave only one-half (rounded do=
wn)
the required threads for any spells they cast in this manner, while great
dragons need not weave any threads for spells they cast using this ability.=
</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Dragons
automatically receive a number of spell matrices equal to their Spellcasting
Step divided by 4 (rounded up). One out of every three of a dragon’s matr=
ices
are Enhanced Matrices and one out of every six are Armored Matrices. For
example, a dragon with a Spellcasting Step of 23 would have 23 / 4 =3D 5.75,
rounded up to 6 spell matrices. Three of these would be standard spell
matrices, two would be Enhanced Matrices and one would be an Armored Matrix.
All of a dragon’s matrices have a Rank equal to that of the maximum Circle
spell the dragon can cast.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Despite the
versatility and power of this ability, not all dragons exploit the full
potential of their spellcasting abilities. With the tainting of astral spac=
e by
the Horrors, the use of Raw Magic is dangerous, even to creatures as powerf=
ul
as dragons. For this reason, many dragons have adopted the more complex for=
ms
of spell magic practiced by other Namegivers.</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>CREATURE
SPELLCASTING</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step Number: R=
ank +
PER</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Type: Magical<=
/p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>The Spellcasti=
ng
power enables creatures to cast spells using raw magic. When casting spells
with this power, creatures are vulnerable to the same Warping and Damage
effects as Namegiver magicians, but they don’t run the same risk of becom=
ing
Horrormarked as Horrors are usually less interested in marking creatures th=
an
in marking more intelligent life forms. Most creatures do not use spell
matrices, but they must weave spell threads where required. Thread Weaving =
is
only required for creatures that need to weave threads (see Player’s Guid=
e, p.
83). To determine the effect of a spell, use the creature’s Willpower Ste=
p.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

