<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:7.5048in'>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:1.7in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:17.0pt'>Summoning</p>

</div>

<div style=3D'direction:ltr;margin-top:.4506in;margin-left:0in;width:7.5048=
in'>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Step: Rank + W=
IL</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Action: Standa=
rd</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt'>Dragons may su=
mmon
any kind of spirit by making a Summoning Test against the spirit’s Spell
Defense. For each result level achieved on the test, the spirit will perform
one service for the dragon summoner. After summoning a spirit, the dragon m=
akes
a Willpower Test, the result of which determines the number of days the spi=
rit
remains in service. For complete information on summoning spirits, see the
Player’s Guide on p. 211.</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p style=3D'margin:0in'>&nbsp;</p>

